mitre_attack_techniques.signature_description: Adversaries may employ various system checks to detect and avoid virtualization and analysis environments.
Adversaries may employ various means to detect and avoid virtualization and analysis environments.
An adversary may attempt to get detailed information about the operating system and hardware, including version, patches, hotfixes, service packs, and architecture.
Adversaries may attempt to get a listing of open application windows.
Adversaries may attempt to get information about running processes on a system.
Adversaries may interact with the Windows Registry to gather information about the system, configuration, and installed software.
Adversaries may communicate using application layer protocols to avoid detection/network filtering by blending in with existing traffic.
Adversaries may communicate using application layer protocols associated with web traffic to avoid detection/network filtering by blending in with existing traffic.
Query firmware table information (likely to detect VMs)
Checks for debuggers (window names)
Contains capabilities to detect virtual machines
PE file has section (not .text) which is very likely to contain packed code (zlib compression ratio < 0.011)
Tries to detect sandboxes / dynamic malware analysis system (registry check)
Query firmware table information (likely to detect VMs)
Checks for debuggers (window names)
Contains capabilities to detect virtual machines
Queries a list of all running drivers
Queries the volume information (name, serial number etc) of a device
Queries the cryptographic machine GUID
Reads software policies
Reads the hosts file
Uses HTTPS
Uses HTTPS for network communication, use the SSL MITM Proxy cookbook for further analysis
Performs DNS lookups
Uses HTTPS
Performs DNS lookups
Uses Windows timers to delay execution
Sample monitors Window changes (e.g. starting applications), analyze the sample with the simulation cookbook
Creates hidden files, links and/or directories
Uses the "uname" system call to query kernel version information (possible evasion)
May sleep (evasive loops) to hinder dynamic analysis
